<!-- 
	Description: An example of a simple XML file
	Note: 
		1. Root Element	: <PlayersProfile>. Also known as document element. There can be only one root element in an XML Document. Root element name can be any valid XML Element name. 
		2. Elements			: <PlayersProfile>, <Player>, <Name> and <Sports>
		3. Attribute 			: id="1" is an attribute associated with the element <Player>
		4. Contents			: "Sachin Ramesh Tendulkar" and "Cricket"
		5. End Tags			: </PlayersProfile>, </Player>, </Name>, </Sports>
-->
<PlayersProfile>
	<Player id="1">
		<Name>Sachin Ramesh Tendulkar</Name>
		<Sports>Cricket</Sports>
	</Player>
</PlayersProfile>
